name: treatment of electronics scrap, metals recovery in copper smelter | metal part of electronics scrap, in copper, anode | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/4349/documentation

The multi-output-process "secondary copper conversion" delivers the co-products "metal values from electric waste, in blister-copper, at converter" and "lead, secondary, from electronic and electric scrap recycling, at plant". The product "metal values from electric waste, …" is an intermediary in the production of secondary gold from electric scrap and is not to be used by the LCA practitioner.  The flow "lead, …" is a by-product of this process that receives part of the burdens allocated. It must not be used to reflect lead.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]

The activity starts with the reception of the elecronics scrap.

Inculdes the processing of e-scrap in the Boliden process by the Kaldo plant and the converter aisle.
category: C:Manufacturing/24:Manufacture of basic metals/242:Manufacture of basic precious and other non-ferrous metals/2420:Manufacture of basic precious and other non-ferrous metals

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data describes a Swedish plant that is singular in the region and ranges worldwide among the big producer. It may be taken as approximation for the global situation
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Conversion of Copper in a Kaldo Converter and treatment in converter aisle.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: see Geography and Technology This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography SE. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
